        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:54PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Wild Horse Point, or 40 miles north of North La Junta,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haswell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for southeastern
Colorado.</instruction>
